Ese enfrentamiento entre los dos tramposos fue muy divertida, son tan lindos~
Aww~, si tan solo los chicos de Seventeen hubieran sido mis compañeros de clase, muchas cosas habrían sido diferentes. Creo que reprobaría todas las materias por estar concentrada solo en ellos XD. Lo bueno es que ellos están en nuestras vidas ahora, a nosotros los desafortunados, que no pudimos crecer con ellos ni tenerlos en nuestros colegios XD
Saben, me pregunto, ¿qué tan bien nos iría en clase si todos ellos fueran nuestros profesores? Seria interesante hacer una prueba y ver si ellos nos pueden enseñar alguna materia (aunque sería difícil concentrarse con tanta belleza junta) XD

author: @loryyy_sv
text:
I was like too young when Boys Over Flowers came out and I'd watched it with my older cousin back then(keep in mind k.culture wasn't even a hit yet) then I'd watch it years later in my first year of highschool when kpop suddenly started rising in popularity.

 So like I think that "*almost paradise~~*" part of the drama's SOO iconic. So I think they don't need to worry about young kids these days not knowing it cuz like, when you're starting in kdrama, I think it's one of those classic ones a kdrama person would recommend. Specially since the internet is much more accessible now with high quality compared to back then. 

We only depended on CDs at the time Lol, worse case scenerio was when you lend it to your classmates and they get scratched a bit, then the quality of the video itself is affected😔. Internet was like for the rich in back then, but even then it wasn't still as good of a quality as we have today...

Edit: also keep in mind that I live in a poor country sooo...

author: @mvu2465
text:
I'm sorry if there are negativities in my comment in the content that I enjoy so much, but I have to ask, sincerely: Can Gose team change their Vietnamese translator, please? 
Starting from the first episode when the Vietsub was added, I and some Vietnamese comments mentioned the wrong pronouns, and then there are several translating mistakes that I can easily point out. Undoubtedly these mistakes come from word-by-word translating, and there are some lines that the translator just simply keeps the English lines, not bothering to translate them. 
For example, in this video, in the line where the caption was about Jeonghan's Adam's apple, the Vietnamese caption was "uvula" in Vietnamese??? 
Another example: The part when Jeonghan called out Joshua, which was originally said: "조슈지 나와", the Vietnamese sub was "Joshuaji and I"???
As a translator myself, these silly little mistakes trigger me a lot. In every episode that has Vietsub until this one, there are at least 2 or so silly mistakes like this. Luckily, these mistakes haven't changed the meaning much, but what if? What if there are more serious translating mistakes in the future that may affect Seventeen and Gose?
I posted a comment in Vietnamese directly to the Vietnamese translator in the last episode, asking the translator to put more effort into the translating process if he/she received translating payment from Gose team. Apparently, there are no changes shown in this episode. To be very honest, there are Vietsub from fans that are: 1. free and 2. accurate and 3. super hilarious, therefore, I see no point of enduring this kind of translating. But V-Carats decided that we should focus on the main channel for the view and other kinds of stuff, so, well :( 
Just change the Vietnamese translator please :(
